(3304, 3678, '1511949260695_data', '{\"id\":\"1511949260695\",\"shortcode\":\"ppb_text\",\"ppb_text_title\":\"Text%20Block\",\"ppb_text_layout\":\"fullwidth\",\"ppb_text_background\":\"\",\"ppb_text_background_parallax\":\"\",\"ppb_text_custom_css\":\"\",\"ppb_text_content\":\"%5Btg_header%20title=%22Mingalabar%22%5D%0A%3Cp%3E%0A%09Myanmar%20(Burma)%20is%20situated%20in%20Southeast%20Asia%20and%20is%20bordered%20on%20the%20north%20and%20northeast%20by%20China%20and%20northwest%20by%20India%20which%20is%20separated%20by%20high%20Himalayas,%20Mt.%20Hkakaborazi%205881%20meters%20and%20many%20more;%20on%20the%20east%20and%20southeast%20by%20Laos%20and%20Thailand%20respectively;%20on%20the%20south%20by%20the%20Andaman%20Sea%20and%20the%20Bay%20of%20Bengal;%20and%20on%20the%20west%20by%20Bangladesh%20and%20India.%20The%20country%20covers%20an%20area%20of%20677,000%20square%20kilometers%20(261,228%20square%20miles),%20ranging%20936%20kilometers%20(581%20miles)%20from%20east%20to%20west%20and%202,051%20kilometers%20(1,275%20miles)%20from%20north%20to%20south.%20Myanmar%20shares%20a%202,185-kilometre%20border%20with%20China.%20The%20second-longest%20border%20is%20shared%20with%20Thailand%20(1,800%20kilometers)%20followed%20by%20India%20(1,463%20kilometers),%20Laos%20(235%20kilometers)%20and%20Bangladesh%20(193%20kilometers).%20Myanmar%20is%20a%20country%20of%20incredible%20variation%20-%20a%20tailor-made%20holiday%20here%20typically%20combines%20unique%20cultural%20wonders,%20trekking%20through%20rural%20villages%20and%20landscapes%20to%20all%20the%20way%20to%20Himalayas,%20rafting%20in%20crystal%20clean%20jade%20color%20Himalayas%20rivers,%20%20relaxation%20on%20tranquil%20beaches%20and%20time%20spent%20adrift%20in%20evocative%20cities,%20where%20every%20corner%20reveals%20yet%20another%20mesmerizing%20highlight.%20To%20say%20that%20your%20visit%20to%20Myanmar%20will%20be%20a%20holiday%20like%20no%20other%20would%20be%20a%20drastic%20understatement.%20Probably%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20greatest%20asset%20is%20its%20people,%20whose%20infectious%20spirit%20and%20genuine%20smiles%20are%20hard%20to%20beat.%0A%3C/p%3E%0A%3Cp%3E%0A%09%3Cstrong%3EHISTORY%3C/strong%3E%3Cbr%3E%0A%09The%20earliest%20known%20primate%20is%20referred%20to%20as%20Pondaung%20Man%20%E2%80%93%20named%20after%20the%20area%20in%20northern%20Myanmar%20where%20he%20was%20found%20%E2%80%93%20who%20lived%20about%2040%20million%20years%20ago.%20More%20recently%20several%20city%20states%20emerged,%20followed%20by%20what%20are%20known%20as%20the%20three%20Myanmar%20Empires.%20The%20earliest%20major%20civilization%20was%20known%20as%20the%20Pyu.%20Later,%20King%20Anawrahta%20of%20Bagan%20(1044-1077AD)%20created%20the%20first%20Myanmar%20Empire.%20The%20second%20Myanmar%20Empire%20was%20created%20by%20King%20Bayinnaung%20of%20the%20Taungoo%20Dynasty%20(1551-1581AD),%20while%20the%20third%20Myanmar%20Empire%20was%20led%20by%20King%20Alaungpaya%20of%20the%20Konbaung%20Dynasty%20(1752-1760AD).%20These%20three%20great%20kings%20are%20well-known%20in%20Myanmar%20history%20for%20their%20bravery%20and%20leadership.%20After%20the%20country%20fell%20under%20British%20rule%20in%201885,%20King%20Thibaw,%20Queen%20Supayalat%20and%20the%20royal%20family%20were%20taken%20to%20Ratanagiri%20in%20India.%20Myanmar%20remained%20a%20British%20colony%20until%20independence%20on%20January%204,%201948.%0A%3C/p%3E%0A%3Cp%3E%0A%09%3Cstrong%3EGEOGRAPHY%3C/strong%3E%3Cbr%3E%0A%09The%20central%20lowlands%20are%20ringed%20by%20steep,%20rugged%20highlands.%20The%20lowest%20point%20is%20the%20Andaman%20Sea%20and%20the%20highest%20point%20is%20Mt%20Hkakabo%20Razi%20in%20Kachin%20State,%20at%205,881%20meters%0A%3C/p%3E%0A%3Cp%3E%0A%09%3Cstrong%3ECLIMATE%3C/strong%3E%3Cbr%3E%0A%09Myanmar%20has%20three%20main%20seasons:%20a%20hot%20season,%20rainy%20season%20and%20cold%20season.%20Hot%20season%20is%20from%20March%20to%20May,%20rainy%20season%20is%20from%20June%20to%20October%20and%20cold%20season%20is%20from%20November%20to%20February.%20The%20tropical%20monsoon%20is%20usually%20cloudy%20and%20rainy,%20while%20hot%20season%20is%20hot%20and%20humid%20and%20the%20cold%20season%20features%20mild%20temperatures%20and%20lower%20humidity.%20Rainfall%20is%20scant%20in%20both%20summer%20and%20winter.%0A%3C/p%3E%0A%3Cp%3E%0A%09%3Cstrong%3ENATURAL%20RESOURCES%3C/strong%3E%3Cbr%3E%0A%09Myanmar%20is%20rich%20in%20natural%20resources,%20including%20petroleum,%20timber,%20tin,%20antimony,%20zinc,%20copper,%20tungsten,%20lead,%20coal,%20marble,%20limestone,%20precious%20stones%20and%20natural%20gas.%0A%3C/p%3E%0A%3Cp%3E%0A%09%3Cstrong%3EPEOPLE%3C/strong%3E%3Cbr%3E%0A%09Myanmar%20is%20made%20up%20of%20135%20national%20races,%20of%20which%20the%20main%20groups%20are%20Kachin,%20Kayah,%20Kayin,%20Chin,%20Bamar,%20Mon,%20Rakhine%20and%20Shan.%20Population%20is%20estimated%20to%20be%20more%20than%2060%20million,%20of%20which%20Bamar%20are%20thought%20to%20make%20up%20about%20two-thirds.%20The%20nationality%20is%20Myanmar.%20Some%20of%20the%20smaller%20ethnic%20groups%20include%20Akha,%20Palaung,%20Padaung,%20Naga,%20Taron%20and%20Eng.%20The%20mains%20religions%20are%20Buddhism,%20Christian%20and%20Muslim.%20The%20major%20language%20is%20Myanmar,%20but%20minority%20ethnic%20groups%20have%20their%20own%20languages.%20%20English%20is%20widely%20spoken%20and%20understood.%0A%3C/p%3E\"}'),
