(2807, 1, '2016-10-08 03:42:04', '2016-10-08 03:42:04', '[tg_header title=\"An Intimate Journey into the Heart of Rural Nepal\" subtitle=\"A Socially Conscious Adventure\"]\r\nMake a lasting difference while living the adventure of a lifetime. More than just a trek, Nepalaya Explorer\'s Community Trek Nepal is a total immersion experience for those searching for more fulfillment from their travel abroad. You will become part of a close-knit team striving to bring medical, social, educational, and economic aid to villages destroyed by the 2015 earthquakes. From your vantage point within these small communities, you will learn about the traitional Nepali way of life while exploring areas largely unfamiliar to international guests.\r\n\r\nPhysical activities are of moderate difficulty and no prior experience is necessary.\r\n\r\n[tg_header title=\"Quick Look\" subtitle=\"Adventure Overview\"]\r\n<strong>Who should go: </strong>Students, outdoor enthusiasts, teachers, anyone wishing to share his or her knowledge on subjects of civic importance, or who would like to have an intimate view of the traditional rural Nepali lifestyle\r\n<strong>Trip Duration: </strong>15 - 30 days\r\n<b>Physical Difficulty: </b>2 of 5\r\n<strong>Activities: </strong>Community service work, community education, cultural immersion, cooking, trekking\r\n<strong>Max. Altitude: </strong>\r\n<strong>Group Size: </strong>2-14\r\n<strong>Accommodations: </strong>Homestay, guesthouse\r\n\r\n[tg_header title=\"You will enjoy:\"]\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Assisting with medical checkups, distribution of medicine, and referrals for follow-up care</li>\r\n 	<li>Constructing a safe and educational children\'s playground, including a multi-sport arena</li>\r\n 	<li>Organizing community workshops on a variety of topics, including: caring for the environment, politics, ecotourism, traffic safety, sex education, water safety and irrigation, civic engagement, and workplace training</li>\r\n 	<li>Helping Nepali teens build outdoor adventure skills in activities such as: rafting, trekking, mountain biking, rock climbing, canyoning, and swimming</li>\r\n 	<li>Learning about and preserving Nepali culture and traditions</li>\r\n 	<li>Discovering Nepali cuisine, recipes, and culinary techniques</li>\r\n 	<li>Educating the community about rubbish collection, recycling, and reducing waste by re-using resources</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[tg_header title=\"Adventure Program\" subtitle=\"15 to 30 Days\"]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nEach Community Trek Nepal is a unique adventure. Where you will go, and exactly which activities you will participate in are dependent on village partners and ongoing recovery efforts. If you would like a detailed itinerary for the dates you will be traveling to Nepal, please contact us for more information.\r\n\r\n[tg_header title=\"Price Includes:\"]\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Domestic transportation</li>\r\n 	<li>Accommodation</li>\r\n 	<li>3 meals daily</li>\r\n 	<li>All associated permits</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[tg_header title=\"Price Does Not Include:\"]\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>International flights and associated taxes</li>\r\n 	<li>Nepali tourist visa</li>\r\n 	<li>Optional (*) activities</li>\r\n 	<li>Alcoholic and specialty beverages</li>\r\n 	<li>Tips for porters and guides</li>\r\n 	<li>Travel and health insurance</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Community Trek Nepal', '<i class=\"fa fa-map-marker\"></i>&nbsp;4-5 Stars Hotel for all trips\r\n<i class=\"fa fa-map-marker\"></i>&nbsp;Chill out on historical town and city of madrid\r\n<i class=\"fa fa-map-marker\"></i>&nbsp;Watch La li ga football match\r\n<i class=\"fa fa-map-marker\"></i>&nbsp;100% Satisfaction guarantee', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'community-trek-nepal', '', '', '2017-03-22 10:50:11', '2017-03-22 10:50:11', '', 0, 'http://themes.themegoods2.com/altair/?post_type=tours&#038;p=2807', 1, 'tours', '', 0),
(2809, 1, '2016-10-08 03:44:25', '2016-10-08 03:44:25', '[tg_header title=\"Discover the real Nepal\" subtitle=\"with Nepalaya Explorer\'s 15-day Absolute Nepal Adventure\"]\r\n\r\nTailored for international visitors looking for an authentic Nepali experience, the Absolute Nepal Adventure traverses a variety of landscapes, from the lush Terai region to the imposing Annapurna range. Guided by Nepalaya Explorer’s expert staff, you will immerse yourself in the diverse cultures who make their home in the Himalaya, trek among the highest mountains in the world, experience whitewater rafting, and observe wildlife up close from the back of an elephant.\r\n\r\nPhysical activities are of moderate difficulty and no prior experience is necessary.\r\n\r\n[tg_header title=\"Quick Look\" subtitle=\"Adventure Overview\"]\r\n\r\n<strong>Best season: </strong>February - May, September - November\r\n<strong>Who should go: </strong>Photographers, outdoor enthusiasts, adventure seekers, families\r\n<strong>Trip Duration: </strong>15 days\r\n<b>Physical Difficulty: </b>2 of 5\r\n<strong>Activities: </strong>Trekking, rafting, sightseeing, Chitwan wildlife safari, mountain flight\r\n<strong>Max. Altitude: </strong>3210m/10,530ft\r\n<strong>Group Size: </strong>2-14\r\n<strong>Accommodations: </strong>Hotel, camping, guesthouse\r\n\r\n[tg_header title=\"You will enjoy:\"]\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>1 1/2 days guided whitewater rafting on the Trisuli River</li>\r\n 	<li>1 1/2 days of safari at Chitwan National Park, including an elephant tour and boat cruise</li>\r\n 	<li>5 days of trekking in the Annapurna Range</li>\r\n 	<li>6 days of guided cultural exploration in Pokhara and the Kathmandu Valley</li>\r\n 	<li>Sunrise Mountain Flight overlooking the Himalaya</li>\r\n 	<li>14 nights accommodation: 13 nights lodging &amp; 1 night camping</li>\r\n 	<li>Nepalaya Explorer private guide</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[tg_header title=\"Adventure Program\" subtitle=\"15 Days in the Real Nepal\"]\r\n\r\n[tg_program title=\"Day 1\" place=\"Arrival: Kathmandu\"]A Nepalaya Explorer representative will pick you up at KTM International Airport, transfer you to your hotel in a private car, and brief you about the trip ahead. Overnight at hotel in Kathmandu (***) [/tg_program]\r\n\r\n[tg_program title=\"Day 2\" place=\"Cultural Exploration: Kathmandu\"]Settle in to Nepal with a guided tour of Swyambhunath and Durbar Square. Overnight at hotel in Kathmandu.[/tg_program]\r\n\r\n[tg_program title=\"Day 3\" place=\"Whitewater Rafting: Trisuli River\"]AM - Pickup at your hotel for the drive to Charaundi (approx. 2 1/2 hours).\r\nPM - Following a safety briefing by Nepalaya Explorer\'s professional rafting crew, put in at Charaundi for a guided raft trip on the Trishuli River (class 3-4).\r\nLater, Nepalaya Explorer\'s multi-talented local guides cook you dinner at our private beach camp on the bank of the Trishuli.\r\nCamp overnight on the beach. Tents, cots, and other camping amenities included.[/tg_program]\r\n\r\n[tg_program title=\"Day 4\" place=\"Arrive: Chitwan National Park\"]AM - Wake up on the beach and enjoy a Nepali River morning.\r\nPM - Drive to Chitwan National Park (approx. 2 1/2 hours). Check in at the lodge and watch the sun set over the jungle. For those who wish, now would be an excellent time for an Elephant Bath!* Dinner and overnight at the lodge (***).\r\n[/tg_program]\r\n\r\n[tg_program title=\"Day 5\" place=\"Wildlife Safari: Chitwan National Park\"]AM - After an early breakfast, indulge in a boat ride on the Rapti/Narayani river to witness crocodiles, gharial, marsh mugger, and other animals and birds.\r\nPM - Following lunch at the lodge, meet the elephant who will be your host for an afternoon jungle safari. Dinner and overnight at the lodge.\r\n[/tg_program]\r\n\r\n[tg_program title=\"Day 6\" place=\"Arrive: Pokhara\"]AM - Drive from Chitwan to Pokhara (approx. 6 hours), passing rice terraces and mountain landscapes.\r\nPM - Your guide will give you a brief orientation of Pokhara\'s Lakeside district and prepare you for the trek ahead. Overnight at guesthouse in Lakeside (***).\r\n[/tg_program]\r\n\r\n[tg_program title=\"Day 7\" place=\"Trekking: Annapurna Range - Hile\"]AM - Depart early for Nayapul by private car (approx. 1 1/2 hours). From Nayapul (alt. 1,011m), where the trek begins, the terrain is moderate and the trail passes through a series of small villages. This short and relatively easy day (approx. 3 hours trekking), allows for a gentle familiarization to the experience of trekking in Nepal and gives you time to acclimate to the altitude.\r\nPM - Overnight at guesthouse in Hile (***).\r\n[/tg_program]\r\n\r\n[tg_program title=\"Day 8\" place=\"Trekking: Annapurna Range - Ghorepani\"]AM - After a hearty breakfast, begin the trek to Ghorepani (approx. 6 hours). Today, we tackle several steep climbs and pass through the most popular village along the Annapurna circuit.\r\nPM - Overnight at guiesthouse in Ghorepani, alt. 2,850m, which boasts magnificent views of the Annapurna range (***).\r\n[/tg_program]\r\n\r\n[tg_program title=\"Day 9\" place=\"Trekking: Annapurna Range - Poonhill &amp; Tadapani\"]AM - Begin the day before dawn with a short walk (approx. 45 minutes) to take in the sunrise at Poonhill. Enjoy the breathtaking panoramic views of many of the famous Himalayan from this historic site, including: Dhaulagiri, Annapurna South, Fishtail, and many more that are nameless and unmeasured.\r\nPM - After our sunrise visit to Poonhill, return to Ghorepani for a hot breakfast and continue onward to Tadapani, alt. 2,630m. Overnight at guesthouse in Tadapani (***).\r\n[/tg_program]\r\n\r\n[tg_program title=\"Day 10\" place=\"Trekking: Annapurna Range - Ghandruk\"]AM - Leaving Tadapani, descend steeply through the lush forest, then continue along gentler terrain as we approach Ghandruk, alt. 2,012m.\r\nPM - In the evening, take time to explore this picturesque Gurung village, learning about the dialect, traditions, culture, costumes and lifestyle of this prominent Nepali ethnic group (***).\r\n[/tg_program]\r\n\r\n[tg_program title=\"Day 11\" place=\"Trekking: Annapurna Range - return to Pokhara\"]AM - Enjoy and easy morning, breakfasting overlooking the Himalayas.\r\nPM - Finish the journey with a gentle descent back to Nayapul, then return to Pokhhara by private car (approx. 1 1/2 hours). In the evening, a good and relaxing surprise awaits us in Pokhara. Overnight at guesthouse in Pokhara (***).\r\n[/tg_program]\r\n\r\n[tg_program title=\"Day 12\" place=\"Relaxation &amp; Exploration: Pokhara\"] Pokhara is a great spot to relax after a mountain trek. Choose any combination of delightful relaxing activities: shopping in Lakeside, boat ride on Pewa Lake, short hike to the Peace Pagoda, visit to the mountaineering museum, paragliding, renting a bike to explore Pokhara and the surrounding area*. Overnight at guesthouse in Pokhara (***).\r\n[/tg_program]\r\n\r\n[tg_program title=\"Day 13\" place=\"Cultural Exploration - Kathmandu\"] AM - Return to Kathmandu by tourist bus (approx. 6 hours). (Flights can be arranged for those wishing for a faster return.*)\r\nPM - Explore Boudhanath, one of the largest stupas in the world, and the surrounding Tibetan Buddhist monestaries. Overnight at hotel in Kathmandu(***).\r\n[/tg_program]\r\n\r\n[tg_program title=\"Day 14\" place=\"Cultural Exploration - Bhaktapur &amp; Patan\"] Accompanied by your guide, visit Bhaktapur and Patan in the Kathmandu Valley, discovering the gods and goddesses honored in Bhaktapur, and thearts and traditional crafts for which Patan is famous around the world. Overnight at hotel in Kathmandu (***).\r\n[/tg_program]\r\n\r\n[tg_program title=\"Day 15\" place=\"Mountain Flight over Mt. Everest &amp; Departure for Home Sweet Home\"] AM - Wake early for one final adventure: a 5:30 AM Mountain Flight (approx. 1 hour duration), an unforgettable airborne tour where you will watch the sun rise at the top of the world.\r\nPM - Time allowing, choose from an assortment of leisure or cultural activities in Kathmandu: shopping, renting a bike to explore the narrow streets of the city and its colorful street markets, visit the Garden of Dreams or choose from another of Kathmandu\'s innumerable cultural landmarks.\r\n[/tg_program]\r\n\r\n*Activities are optional and are not included in the package price.\r\n\r\n[tg_header title=\"Price Includes:\"]\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>13 days lodging and breakfast at hotels and guesthouses</li>\r\n 	<li>All meals during trekking and rafting expeditions</li>\r\n 	<li>Non-alcoholic drinks during rafting expedition</li>\r\n 	<li>All ground transportation, including private driver or tourist coach</li>\r\n 	<li>All visits and outdoor activities not labeled optional (*)</li>\r\n 	<li>Private guide traveling with you at all times</li>\r\n 	<li>Porters while trekking</li>\r\n 	<li>All trekking and river permits</li>\r\n 	<li>Mountain Flight</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[tg_header title=\"Price Does Not Include:\"]\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>International flights and associated taxes</li>\r\n 	<li>Optional (*) activities</li>\r\n 	<li>Lunch and dinner outside of designated trekking / rafting expeditions</li>\r\n 	<li>Alcohol and specialty beverages</li>\r\n 	<li>Tips for porters and guides</li>\r\n 	<li>Travel and health insurance</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Absolute Nepal Adventure', '<i class=\"fa fa-map-marker\"></i>&nbsp;4-5 Stars Hotel for all trips\r\n<i class=\"fa fa-map-marker\"></i>&nbsp;Chill out on historical town and city\r\n<i class=\"fa fa-map-marker\"></i>&nbsp;Sail the biggest lake of Turkey\r\n<i class=\"fa fa-map-marker\"></i>&nbsp;100% Satisfaction guarantee', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'absolute-nepal-adventure', '', '', '2017-11-22 07:34:19', '2017-11-22 07:34:19', '', 0, 'http://themes.themegoods2.com/altair/?post_type=tours&#038;p=2809', 0, 'tours', '', 0),
