(3374, 3, '2016-06-20 16:18:12', '2016-06-20 16:18:12', '[tg_header title=\"Raft, Kayak, Explore\" subtitle=\"A Wet &amp; Wild Family-Friendly Adventure\"]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSpringing from the high slopes of Machhapuchhre, \"Fishtail Mountain,\" the lower Seti River offers superb forest scenery and gentle rapids.\r\n\r\nStudent groups, families, with children, or adults looking for a low-key adventure will enjoy relaxing along the sandy beaches, swimming in the warm water, and exploring the riverbanks. Wildlife enthusiasts will be delighted by the variety of animals found in this lush river basin.\r\n\r\nThe Seti offers a two-day rafting adventure just a short drive from Pokhara (52 km) or Kathmandu (154 km). Combine the Seti River Adventure with a wildlife safari in Chitwan National Park or a Jalbire Canyoning Expedition before continuing onward to your next adventure.\r\n\r\nDeluxe trips are available and may appeal to honeymooners, couples celebrating an important anniversary, or anyone wishing to travel in style. Enjoy candlelit dinners on the beach and a glass of wine under the star-swept sky of the Nepali night.\r\n\r\n[tg_header title=\"Quick Look\" subtitle=\"Adventure Overview\"]\r\n\r\n<strong>Best Season: </strong>February - May, September - January (or choose the rainy season for Monsoon Blast)\r\n<strong>Trip Duration: </strong>2 days\r\n<b>Difficulty: </b>Grade 2-3\r\n<strong>Skill Level:</strong> Appropriate for beginners, families with children, retirees, honeymooners, student groups &amp; organizations\r\n<strong>Put-in: </strong>Damauli Bridge\r\n<strong>Take-out: </strong>Ghaighat (low water) or Narayanghat (high water)\r\n<strong>Transportation: </strong>Private van from Kathmandu or Pokhara\r\n<strong>Activities: </strong>Trekking, rafting, sightseeing, Chitwan wildlife safari option\r\n<strong>Options: </strong>Deluxe or Standard Trip\r\n<strong>Accommodations: </strong>Tented camping\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[tg_header title=\"Adventure Program\" subtitle=\"2 Days of Scenic, Splashy Fun\"]\r\n\r\n[tg_program title=\"Arrival\" place=\"Kathmandu\"]Take a deep breath and prepare to confront the confusion of Tribhuvan International Airport. After clearing immigration and customs, hang on to your gear and push past the would-be airport porters to the passenger pick-up area outside the building. This can be pretty confusing, with taxi drivers looking for fares, hotel touts desperately seeking customers, and a large crowd just milling around - welcome to Asia!\r\n\r\nDon\'t worry, a Nepalaya Explorer representative will be there to meet you at the airport and escort you to your hotel. In the afternoon, you will have time to venture into the bustle of this amazing city for your first taste of Kathmandu. Walking around this ancient city is like being in the world\'s biggest outdoor museum. We recommend a good guide book (available at a reasonable price at any of Kathmandu\'s many book shops), then grabbing a taxi or a rickshaw, or setting out on foot to visit some of the incredible temples, stupas, and squares that make up this most vibrant of capitals. From observing prayer wheels turning at the Buddhist stupa Bouddhanath, to perhaps gaining a glimpse of the Living Goddess in Durbar Square, there are endless ways to pass the day. A great way to finish it off is people watching, cold drink in hand, on one of the many terrace cafes.\r\n\r\nAt 6 pm, we\'ll meet for a pre-departure briefing, then head off to one of Kathmandu\'s finer restaurants to share a meal.[/tg_program]\r\n\r\n[tg_program title=\"Day 1\" place=\"Seti River\"]AM: Rise early and gather your things. Nepalaya Explorer\'s driver will shuttle you to the put-in (4 hours from Kathmandu or 2 hours from Pokhara), where your river crew is waiting to welcome you. Your trip leader introduces you to the crew and the rafting equipment, then everyone is outfitted with rafting gear. The trip leader and safety kayaker brief the group about whitewater safety and paddling technique while the guides tie the equipment into the rafts. (This is quite a thing to witness - twenty years of running rivers have taught us a lot, not the least of which is loading a raft so the load stays put.)\r\n\r\nRafting the Seti with Nepalaya Explorer isn\'t just a vacation. It\'s an education in water sports as well as an exploration of the river highway - our guides make sure to explain the finer points of paddling in whitewater and teach you how to stay in the raft as it bucks through the rapids.\r\n\r\nSoon enough, we are navigating the scenic Seti River basin. The river is lined by white sand beaches, beyond which the lush forest slopes upwards. After a couple gentle rapids, it\'s time for lunch. Then we\'re back on the river, with more rapids to come before we reach our campsite. The camp is tastefully sculptured into a huge eddyline,  and high walls overlooking the Seti River. Beyond, behind the tents, the beach merges with a Gurung village.\r\n\r\nPM: Share a candlelit dinner with your family or fellow river guests. Enjoy a glass of wine under the stars before retiring into your tent to enjoy a well-earned rest.[/tg_program]\r\n\r\n[tg_program title=\"Day 2\" place=\"Seti River\"]Awake to a hearty breakfast prepared by your guides. Will you take tea or coffee? We pack up camp, leaving only our footprints in the sand. This day, the Seti offers bigger rapids and more excitement, but is still appropriate for beginners. Following the confluence of the Seti and the Trisuli Rivers, the river widens substantially and the current picks up the pace. From here, we float easily with the current until we reach the take-out. Our crew divides in teams to prepare lunch and pack the gear. We take a couple of group photos with the crew. Till we meet again![/tg_program]\r\n\r\n[tg_program title=\"Add-on Option #1\" place=\"Canyoning\"]If you\'re still hungry for adventure when it\'s time the get off the river, then the Jalbire Canyoning Adventure may be just up your alley. Located only 45 minutes upstream along the Trisuli River, Jalbire is one of the longest waterfalls in Nepal. This family-friendly canyoning experience can be customized to fit a group of any ability level. Visit the Jalbire Canyoning Adventure page or email us for more information.[/tg_program]\r\n\r\n[tg_program title=\"Add-on Option #2\" place=\"Safari\"]After getting off the river, keep heading South to Chitwan National Park, to finish off your trip with a stay at the luxurious Tiger Tops Lodge and Camp. Set in the heart of the park, the Lodge offers fantastic bird watching opportunities, not to mention occasional sightings of the Royal Bengal Tiger, rhino, and a rich array of other wildlife. Naturalists are on hand with their seemingly endless supply of knowledge to answer your queries.\r\n\r\nThe Lodge is made entirely of local materials and blends beautifully with its environment. Enjoy a range of activities, from elephant safaris to jungle walks, to plain old relaxing in the serene surroundings of the Lodge. Meals are all-inclusive and the menu includes delicious western as well as Nepali dishes. Accommodation is in spacious safari tents with twin beds and separate hot and cold showers.\r\n[/tg_program]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n[tg_header title=\"Price Includes:\" subtitle=\"Deluxe\"]\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Licensed English-speaking local guides and safety kayakers, highly trained and safety certified to international standards in: Rescue 3 WRT, Nepal Red Cross CPR, High Peak First Aid, International Wilderness First-Aid, IRF trained, and highly knowledgable about the local area</li>\r\n	<li>High-quality, ISO certified rafting and kayaking equipment and full personal outfitting, including: paddles, helmets, PFDs (life jackets) dry tops, wetsuits (youth sizes available), dry bags, and pelican boxes for valuables such as cameras</li>\r\n	<li>Two nights at a *** hotel in Kathmandu, one day sightseeing in Kathmandu, airport pickup and drop-off</li>\r\n	<li>Camping accommodation, including: shelters, personal tents, air mattresses, sleeping bags, pillow, picnic umbrella, table and chairs, toilet tents</li>\r\n	<li>Three meals daily: a hearty breakfast, leisurely lunch, and dinner with a complementary glass of wine. While on the river, guides prepare traditional Nepali and western cuisine, made with fresh, organic ingredients.</li>\r\n	<li>Complementary beverages, including bottled water</li>\r\n	<li>Round trip transportation via private car</li>\r\n	<li>River permits</li>\r\n	<li>Village sightseeing</li>\r\n	<li>Adventure Industry standard first aid kits</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[tg_header title=\"Price Includes:\" subtitle=\"Standard\"]\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Licensed English-speaking local guides and safety kayakers, highly trained and safety certified to international standards in: Rescue 3 WRT, Nepal Red Cross CPR, High Peak First Aid, International Wilderness First-Aid, IRF trained, and highly knowledgable about the local area</li>\r\n	<li>High-quality, ISO certified rafting and kayaking equipment and full personal outfitting, including: paddles, helmets, PFDs (life jackets) dry tops, wetsuits (youth sizes available), dry bags, and pelican boxes for valuables such as cameras</li>\r\n	<li>Two nights at at tourist hotel in Kathmandu, one day sightseeing in Kathmandu, airport pickup and drop-off</li>\r\n	<li>Camping accommodation, including: shelters, personal tents, air mattresses, sleeping bags, toilet tents</li>\r\n	<li>Three meals daily: a hearty breakfast, leisurely lunch, and dinner with a complementary glass of wine. While on the river, guides prepare traditional Nepali and western cuisine, made with fresh, organic ingredients.</li>\r\n	<li>Complementary beverages, including bottled water</li>\r\n	<li>Round trip transportation via private car</li>\r\n	<li>River permits</li>\r\n	<li>Village sightseeing</li>\r\n	<li>Adventure Industry standard first aid kits</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[tg_header title=\"Price Does Not Include:\"]\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>International flights and associated taxes</li>\r\n	<li>Items of personal nature (toiletries, clothing, camera, etc.)</li>\r\n	<li>Alcohol and specialty beverages</li>\r\n	<li>Tips for porters and guides</li>\r\n	<li>Travel and health insurance</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[tg_header title=\"What to Bring:\"]\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Your sense of adventure (and humor!)</li>\r\n	<li>River shorts or swim costume</li>\r\n	<li>Chacos or similar sandals that secure your heal (trainers or sneakers are also suitable for rafting)</li>\r\n	<li>Long sleeved shirt to wear under your life vest to keep the sun off, preferably a quick-dry, synthetic fiber</li>\r\n	<li>Baseball cap (or similar) to wear under your helmet to keep the sun off</li>\r\n	<li>Wide-brimmed sun hat to wear on the bank</li>\r\n	<li>Sunglasses</li>\r\n	<li>Chums for fastening your sunglasses</li>\r\n	<li>Eye glasses or contact lenses (disposable lenses are ideal) - please let your guide know if you wear glasses in advance of your trip</li>\r\n	<li>Nalgene or other sturdy water bottle</li>\r\n	<li>Carabiner for fastening water bottle to your boat</li>\r\n	<li>Thermal top - meadium weight to heavyweight Capilene or polypropylene is the best choice</li>\r\n	<li>Waterproof sunscreen and lip balm (minimum SPF15)</li>\r\n	<li>Lightweight long trousers</li>\r\n	<li>Lightweight long sleeved shirt</li>\r\n	<li>Fleece jacket or sweater</li>\r\n	<li>Ladies, please bring a long skirt or sarong to wear in the company of locals or while visiting holy places</li>\r\n	<li>Shoes or boots for exploring off the river</li>\r\n	<li>Toiletries: toothbrush, toothpaste, biodegradable soap, shampoo, etc.</li>\r\n	<li>Moisturizer</li>\r\n	<li>Hand wipes or hand sanitizer</li>\r\n	<li>3-season sleeping bag and thermo rest sleeping mat if you prefer to use your own (we provide a complementary set upon request)</li>\r\n	<li>Travel pillow</li>\r\n	<li>Small pack towel</li>\r\n	<li>Headlamp or hand torch with spare batteries</li>\r\n	<li>Insect repellent</li>\r\n	<li>Any medications you may be taking</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[tg_header title=\"What to Bring:\"]\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A book or journal for recording river memories and inspirations</li>\r\n	<li>Sketchpad</li>\r\n	<li>Photographic, GOPRO, or video equipment. We recommend bringing your own waterproof casing and a cleaning kit as we will be camping in the sand. Don\'t forget a spare memory card or plenty of film, as well as spare batteries.</li>\r\n	<li>Waterproof disposable camera to document the \"action\" on the raft</li>\r\n	<li>Pocket knife or multi-tool</li>\r\n	<li>iPod or other portable music device (your guide will pack the speakers)</li>\r\n	<li>Binoculars if you are a bird watcher</li>\r\n	<li>In short, we advise you to pack as light as possible, without skimping on the essentials.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[tg_header title=\"Personal Spending:\"]\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The only money you will need on the excursion is for meals in town, souvenirs, personal items and the beer kitty for the raft trip if you drink. ATMs are available in larger towns.</li>\r\n	<li>If you wish to pass on a gratuity to your team, we leave this entirely up to you, but kindly suggest that if you do choose to give, give to the group as a whole so that the team can share with those who are working behind the scenes to make your trip complete.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Seti River Adventure', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'seti-river-adventure', '', '', '2016-07-22 13:00:34', '2016-07-22 13:00:34', '', 0, 'http://dac.technocreates.net/nepalayaexplorer/?post_type=tours&#038;p=3374', 0, 'tours', '', 0),
(3375, 3, '2016-06-20 15:49:53', '2016-06-20 15:49:53', '[tg_header title=\"Discover the real Nepal\" subtitle=\"with Nepalaya Explorer\'s 15-day Absolute Nepal Adventure\"]\r\n\r\nTailored for international visitors looking for an authentic Nepali experience, the Absolute Nepal Adventure traverses a variety of landscapes, from the lush Terai region to the imposing Annapurna range. Guided by Nepalaya Explorer’s expert staff, you will immerse yourself in the diverse cultures who make their home in the Himalaya, trek among the highest mountains in the world, experience whitewater rafting, and observe wildlife up close from the back of an elephant.\r\n\r\nPhysical activities are of moderate difficulty and no prior experience is necessary.\r\n\r\n[tg_header title=\"Quick Look\" subtitle=\"Adventure Overview\"]\r\n\r\n<strong>Best season: </strong>February - May, September - November\r\n<strong>Who should go: </strong>Photographers, outdoor enthusiasts, adventure seekers, families\r\n<strong>Trip Duration: </strong>15 days\r\n<b>Physical Difficulty: </b>2 of 5\r\n<strong>Activities: </strong>Trekking, rafting, sightseeing, Chitwan wildlife safari, mountain flight\r\n<strong>Max. Altitude: </strong>3210m/10,530ft\r\n<strong>Group Size: </strong>2-14\r\n<strong>Accommodations: </strong>Hotel, camping, guesthouse\r\n\r\n[tg_header title=\"You will enjoy:\"]\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>1 1/2 days guided whitewater rafting on the Trisuli River</li>\r\n	<li>1 1/2 days of safari at Chitwan National Park, including an elephant tour and boat cruise</li>\r\n	<li>5 days of trekking in the Annapurna Range</li>\r\n	<li>6 days of guided cultural exploration in Pokhara and the Kathmandu Valley</li>\r\n	<li>Sunrise Mountain Flight overlooking the Himalaya</li>\r\n	<li>14 nights accommodation: 13 nights lodging &amp; 1 night camping</li>\r\n	<li>Nepalaya Explorer private guide</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[tg_header title=\"Adventure Program\" subtitle=\"15 Days in the Real Nepal\"]\r\n\r\n[tg_program title=\"Day 1\" place=\"Arrival: Kathmandu\"]A Nepalaya Explorer representative will pick you up at KTM International Airport, transfer you to your hotel in a private car, and brief you about the trip ahead. Overnight at hotel in Kathmandu (***) [/tg_program]\r\n\r\n[tg_program title=\"Day 2\" place=\"Cultural Exploration: Kathmandu\"]Settle in to Nepal with a guided tour of Swyambhunath and Durbar Square. Overnight at hotel in Kathmandu.[/tg_program]\r\n\r\n[tg_program title=\"Day 3\" place=\"Whitewater Rafting: Trisuli River\"]AM - Pickup at your hotel for the drive to Charaundi (approx. 2 1/2 hours).\r\nPM - Following a safety briefing by Nepalaya Explorer\'s professional rafting crew, put in at Charaundi for a guided raft trip on the Trishuli River (class 3-4).\r\nLater, Nepalaya Explorer\'s multi-talented local guides cook you dinner at our private beach camp on the bank of the Trishuli.\r\nCamp overnight on the beach. Tents, cots, and other camping amenities included.[/tg_program]\r\n\r\n[tg_program title=\"Day 4\" place=\"Arrive: Chitwan National Park\"]AM - Wake up on the beach and enjoy a Nepali River morning.\r\nPM - Drive to Chitwan National Park (approx. 2 1/2 hours). Check in at the lodge and watch the sun set over the jungle. For those who wish, now would be an excellent time for an Elephant Bath!* Dinner and overnight at the lodge (***).\r\n[/tg_program]\r\n\r\n[tg_program title=\"Day 5\" place=\"Wildlife Safari: Chitwan National Park\"]AM - After an early breakfast, indulge in a boat ride on the Rapti/Narayani river to witness crocodiles, gharial, marsh mugger, and other animals and birds.\r\nPM - Following lunch at the lodge, meet the elephant who will be your host for an afternoon jungle safari. Dinner and overnight at the lodge.\r\n[/tg_program]\r\n\r\n[tg_program title=\"Day 6\" place=\"Arrive: Pokhara\"]AM - Drive from Chitwan to Pokhara (approx. 6 hours), passing rice terraces and mountain landscapes.\r\nPM - Your guide will give you a brief orientation of Pokhara\'s Lakeside district and prepare you for the trek ahead. Overnight at guesthouse in Lakeside (***).\r\n[/tg_program]\r\n\r\n[tg_program title=\"Day 7\" place=\"Trekking: Annapurna Range - Hile\"]AM - Depart early for Nayapul by private car (approx. 1 1/2 hours). From Nayapul (alt. 1,011m), where the trek begins, the terrain is moderate and the trail passes through a series of small villages. This short and relatively easy day (approx. 3 hours trekking), allows for a gentle familiarization to the experience of trekking in Nepal and gives you time to acclimate to the altitude.\r\nPM - Overnight at guesthouse in Hile (***).\r\n[/tg_program]\r\n\r\n[tg_program title=\"Day 8\" place=\"Trekking: Annapurna Range - Ghorepani\"]AM - After a hearty breakfast, begin the trek to Ghorepani (approx. 6 hours). Today, we tackle several steep climbs and pass through the most popular village along the Annapurna circuit.\r\nPM - Overnight at guiesthouse in Ghorepani, alt. 2,850m, which boasts magnificent views of the Annapurna range (***).\r\n[/tg_program]\r\n\r\n[tg_program title=\"Day 9\" place=\"Trekking: Annapurna Range - Poonhill &amp; Tadapani\"]AM - Begin the day before dawn with a short walk (approx. 45 minutes) to take in the sunrise at Poonhill. Enjoy the breathtaking panoramic views of many of the famous Himalayan from this historic site, including: Dhaulagiri, Annapurna South, Fishtail, and many more that are nameless and unmeasured.\r\nPM - After our sunrise visit to Poonhill, return to Ghorepani for a hot breakfast and continue onward to Tadapani, alt. 2,630m. Overnight at guesthouse in Tadapani (***).\r\n[/tg_program]\r\n\r\n[tg_program title=\"Day 10\" place=\"Trekking: Annapurna Range - Ghandruk\"]AM - Leaving Tadapani, descend steeply through the lush forest, then continue along gentler terrain as we approach Ghandruk, alt. 2,012m.\r\nPM - In the evening, take time to explore this picturesque Gurung village, learning about the dialect, traditions, culture, costumes and lifestyle of this prominent Nepali ethnic group (***).\r\n[/tg_program]\r\n\r\n[tg_program title=\"Day 11\" place=\"Trekking: Annapurna Range - return to Pokhara\"]AM - Enjoy and easy morning, breakfasting overlooking the Himalayas.\r\nPM - Finish the journey with a gentle descent back to Nayapul, then return to Pokhhara by private car (approx. 1 1/2 hours). In the evening, a good and relaxing surprise awaits us in Pokhara. Overnight at guesthouse in Pokhara (***).\r\n[/tg_program]\r\n\r\n[tg_program title=\"Day 12\" place=\"Relaxation &amp; Exploration: Pokhara\"] Pokhara is a great spot to relax after a mountain trek. Choose any combination of delightful relaxing activities: shopping in Lakeside, boat ride on Pewa Lake, short hike to the Peace Pagoda, visit to the mountaineering museum, paragliding, renting a bike to explore Pokhara and the surrounding area*. Overnight at guesthouse in Pokhara (***).\r\n[/tg_program]\r\n\r\n[tg_program title=\"Day 13\" place=\"Cultural Exploration - Kathmandu\"] AM - Return to Kathmandu by tourist bus (approx. 6 hours). (Flights can be arranged for those wishing for a faster return.*)\r\nPM - Explore Boudhanath, one of the largest stupas in the world, and the surrounding Tibetan Buddhist monestaries. Overnight at hotel in Kathmandu(***).\r\n[/tg_program]\r\n\r\n[tg_program title=\"Day 14\" place=\"Cultural Exploration - Bhaktapur &amp; Patan\"] Accompanied by your guide, visit Bhaktapur and Patan in the Kathmandu Valley, discovering the gods and goddesses honored in Bhaktapur, and thearts and traditional crafts for which Patan is famous around the world. Overnight at hotel in Kathmandu (***).\r\n[/tg_program]\r\n\r\n[tg_program title=\"Day 15\" place=\"Mountain Flight over Mt. Everest &amp; Departure for Home Sweet Home\"] AM - Wake early for one final adventure: a 5:30 AM Mountain Flight (approx. 1 hour duration), an unforgettable airborne tour where you will watch the sun rise at the top of the world.\r\nPM - Time allowing, choose from an assortment of leisure or cultural activities in Kathmandu: shopping, renting a bike to explore the narrow streets of the city and its colorful street markets, visit the Garden of Dreams or choose from another of Kathmandu\'s innumerable cultural landmarks.\r\n[/tg_program]\r\n\r\n*Activities are optional and are not included in the package price.\r\n\r\n[tg_header title=\"Price Includes:\"]\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>13 days lodging and breakfast at hotels and guesthouses</li>\r\n	<li>All meals during trekking and rafting expeditions</li>\r\n	<li>Non-alcoholic drinks during rafting expedition</li>\r\n	<li>All ground transportation, including private driver or tourist coach</li>\r\n	<li>All visits and outdoor activities not labeled optional (*)</li>\r\n	<li>Private guide traveling with you at all times</li>\r\n	<li>Porters while trekking</li>\r\n	<li>All trekking and river permits</li>\r\n	<li>Mountain Flight</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[tg_header title=\"Price Does Not Include:\"]\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>International flights and associated taxes</li>\r\n	<li>Optional (*) activities</li>\r\n	<li>Lunch and dinner outside of designated trekking / rafting expeditions</li>\r\n	<li>Alcohol and specialty beverages</li>\r\n	<li>Tips for porters and guides</li>\r\n	<li>Travel and health insurance</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Absolute Nepal Adventure', '<i class=\"fa fa-map-marker\"></i>&nbsp;4-5 Stars Hotel for all trips\r\n<i class=\"fa fa-map-marker\"></i>&nbsp;Chill out on historical town and city\r\n<i class=\"fa fa-map-marker\"></i>&nbsp;Sail the biggest lake of Turkey\r\n<i class=\"fa fa-map-marker\"></i>&nbsp;100% Satisfaction guarantee', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '2809-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-06-20 15:49:53', '2016-06-20 15:49:53', '', 2809, 'http://dac.technocreates.net/nepalayaexplorer/2016/06/20/2809-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
