d in the evening return to set camp in the village of Jalberi. [/tg_program]\n\n[tg_header title=\"Price Includes:\"]\n<ul>\n	<li>State-of-the-art, international name-brand ISO-certified canyoning euipment, including wetsuit, specialized harness with PVC slider seat, PFD, helmet, splash top, ropes, carabiners, and figure eights.</li>\n	<li>Licensed professional English-speaking local guides, highly trained and certified to national and international standards in canyoning techniques, advanced rope work, Swift Water Rescue 3, Nepal Red Cross CPR, and wilderness first aid</li>\n	<li>Lunch and beverages</li>\n	<li>Round trip transportation</li>\n	<li>Adventure industry standard first aid kit</li>\n</ul>\n[tg_header title=\"Price Does Not Include:\"]\n<ul>\n	<li>International flights and associated taxes</li>\n	<li>Unrelated transportation, visas, travel documents, etc.</li>\n	<li>Items of personal nature (toiletries, clothing, camera, etc.)</li>\n	<li>Alcohol and junk food</li>\n	<li>Bottled mineral water</li>\n	<li>Tips for porters and guides</li>\n	<li>Personal travel and health insurance</li>\n	<li>Kayaks - can be rented upon request. Please inquire.</li>\n	<li>Photos - Professional trip photos may be available at a small additional charge. Please inquire.</li>\n</ul>\n[tg_header title=\"Packing Aid:\"]\n<ul>\n	<li>Your sense of adventure (and humor!)</li>\n	<li>Shorts</li>\n	<li>Swim Suit</li>\n	<li>Chacos or similar sport sandals that secure your heal</li>\n	<li>Track pants (comfortable, loose-fitting, preferably synthetic)</li>\n	<li>Jacket (waterproof shell)</li>\n	<li>Socks</li>\n	<li>Hiking boots</li>\n	<li>Warm hat (in cooler seasons)</li>\n	<li>Towel</li>\n	<li>Baseball cap (or similar) to wear under your helmet to keep the sun off</li>\n	<li>Wide-brimmed sun hat to wear on the bank</li>\n	<li>Sunglasses</li>\n	<li>Chums for fastening your sunglasses</li>\n	<li>Eye glasses or contact lenses (disposable lenses are ideal) - please let your guide know if you wear glasses in advance of your trip</li>\n	<li>Waterproof sunscreen and lip balm (minimum SPF15)</li>\n	<li>Any medications you may be taking</li>\n	<li>Personal first aid kit</li>\n	<li>Water bottle</li>\n	<li>Waterproof camera or GOPRO</li>\n	<li>A little cash for treats and tips</li>\n</ul>\n[tg_header title=\"Personal Spending:\"]\n<ul>\n	<li>The only money you will need on the excursion is for meals in town, souvenirs, personal items and the beer kitty for the raft trip if you drink. ATMs are available in larger towns.</li>\n	<li>If you wish to pass on a gratuity to your team, we leave this entirely up to you, but kindly suggest that if you do choose to give, give to the group as a whole so that the team can share with those who are working behind the scenes to make your trip complete.</li>\n</ul>', 'Jalberi Canyoning Course', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '3420-autosave-v1', '', '', '2016-08-07 23:10:19', '2016-08-07 23:10:19', '', 3420, 'http://dac.technocreates.net/nepalayaexplorer/2016/08/07/3420-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(3433, 3, '2016-08-07 23:24:58', '2016-08-07 23:24:58', '[tg_header title=\"Canyoning Fun for the Whole Family\" subtitle=\"prepare to get wet\"]\n\nFor anyone looking to get off the beaten track, the Jalbire Canyoning One-Day Adventure is a cool, splashy reprieve from the bustle of Kathmandu.\n\nNepalaya Explorer\'s certified, professional guides will guide you down a stunning descent of the famous Jalberi waterfall. Deep pools, pristine cascades, and lush scenery will make this an unforgettable adventure. You are sure to learn new skills and build confidence as you descend the canyon, and maybe conquer a few fears.\n\nSuitable for families and people of moderate physical ability.\n\n[tg_header title=\"Quick Look\" subtitle=\"Adventure Overview\"]\n\n<strong>Best Season: </strong>March - June, August - November\n<strong>Trip Duration: </strong>1 day\n<b>Difficulty: </b>Mild - Moderate\n<strong>Skill Level:</strong> Adventure Seekers, Outdoor Enthusiasts, Families\n<strong>Location: </strong>Jalberi\n<strong>Transportation:</strong> Bus from Kathmandu (approx. 1 hr)\n<strong>Activities: </strong>Canyoning\n<strong>Group Size: </strong>\n<strong>Accommodations: </strong>N/A\n\n<strong>2016 Departure Dates: </strong>\n<ul>\n	<li>7, 10, 13, 16, 19, 22, 25, 28 March</li>\n	<li>3, 6, 9, 12, 15, 18, 21, 24 April</li>\n	<li>4, 7, 10, 13, 16, 19, 22, 25, 28, 31 May</li>\n	<li>3, 6, 10, 15, 20 June</li>\n	<li>25, 30 August</li>\n	<li>3, 6, 9, 12, 15, 18, 25, 28 September</li>\n	<li>1, 3, 6, 9, 12, 15, 18, 22, 25, 28, 31 October</li>\n	<li>2, 5, 8, 11, 14, 17, 22, 25 November</li>\n</ul>\n[tg_header title=\"Adventure Program\"]\n\n[tg_program title=\"One-Day Jalberi Canyoning\" place=\"(approx. 4 hrs. activity)\"]\n\nWe will start the day early 7am. We take a drive from Kathmandu to Jalberi Canyoning spot by private car or tourist bus on a highway road, enjoying the view of Himalayas, hilly areas, terraces paddy fields, passing villages both side of the road, creeks and rivers. Quick break for breakfast in one of the finer local restaurant. At Jalberi canyoning crew will greetings you, your trip leader will brief you and fitted you with wetsuit, harness, life jacket and helmet.  We walk 30 minutes to get the waterfall where you face with 130 miters fall with spectacular view of lush jungle and river below. We do have 8 waterfalls; however we do not run all of them because for 130 miters you do need previous experience and during our canyoning course we run that in the end of the course, check out “Canyoning Course”. Before we slip, slide and abseil down your leader will brief and train you. We use a simple dry pitch for instruction and practice. After safety briefing &amp; demonstration start learning how to abseil and rock climbing. After everyone feels confident and gear is triple checked by your guide, we are ready to go…\n\nRest of your team fix all the anchors and checked the water level. Friendly amount of water level allow us to start with slide down into the deep pool. Our leader will always be at the top with you, providing instruction &amp; encouragement as he helps you descend your way down the waterfalls as smooth and safe way, and rest of the crew securing your lines and bottom belay with motivating words as well as taking photos if you have been request. The largest waterfall we run is about 26 meters. Sometimes, we slide and sometimes we jump directly into the clear pools below. If you ever find it too difficult to abseil yourself, then our crew are prepared to take over and abseil you down from behind. In the unusual chance that fear totally overcomes you - there is always the chance to walk down and skip the one you are not confident to do it. Picnic Lunch set up middle of the canyon where you can enjoy the amazing Mother Nature’s and waterfalls sounds or might be in one of the local house in village. After leisurely lunch we continue our rest of the canyoning. Actual canyoning exploration takes 4 hours. Have a quick drink’s and then it is time for us to drive to your next adventure.[/tg_program]\n\n[tg_header title=\"Price Includes:\"]\n<ul>\n	<li>State-of-the-art, international name-brand ISO-certified canyoning euipment, including wetsuit, specialized harness with PVC slider seat, PFD, helmet, splash top, ropes, carabiners, and figure eights.</li>\n	<li>Licensed professional English-speaking local guides, highly trained and certified to national and international standards in canyoning techniques, advanced rope work, Swift Water Rescue 3, Nepal Red Cross CPR, and wilderness first aid</li>\n	<li>Lunch and beverages</li>\n	<li>Round trip transportation</li>\n	<li>Adventure industry standard first aid kit</li>\n</ul>\n[tg_header title=\"Price Does Not Include:\"]\n<ul>\n	<li>International flights and associated taxes</li>\n	<li>Unrelated transportation, visas, travel documents, etc.</li>\n	<li>Items of personal nature (toiletries, clothing, camera, etc.)</li>\n	<li>Alcohol and junk food</li>\n	<li>Bottled mineral water</li>\n	<li>Tips for porters and guides</li>\n	<li>Personal travel and health insurance</li>\n	<li>Kayaks - can be rented upon request. Please inquire.</li>\n	<li>Photos - Professional trip photos may be available at a small additional charge. Please inquire.</li>\n</ul>\n[tg_header title=\"Packing Aid:\"]\n\n&nbsp;\n<ul>\n	<li>Shorts</li>\n	<li>Swim Suit</li>\n	<li>Chacos or similar sport sandals that secure your heal</li>\n	<li>Track pants (comfortable, loose-fitting, preferably synthetic)</li>\n	<li>Jacket (waterproof shell)</li>\n	<li>Socks</li>\n	<li>Hiking boots</li>\n	<li>Warm hat (in cooler seasons)</li>\n	<li>Towel</li>\n	<li>Baseball cap (or similar) to wear under your helmet to keep the sun off</li>\n	<li>Wide-brimmed sun hat to wear on the bank</li>\n	<li>Sunglasses</li>\n	<li>Chums for fastening your sunglasses</li>\n	<li>Eye glasses or contact lenses (disposable lenses are ideal) - please let your guide know if you wear glasses in advance of your trip</li>\n	<li>Waterproof sunscreen and lip balm (minimum SPF15)</li>\n	<li>Any medications you may be taking</li>\n	<li>Personal first aid kit</li>\n	<li>Water bottle</li>\n	<li>Waterproof camera or GOPRO</li>\n	<li>A little cash for treats and tips</li>\n</ul>', 'Jalberi Canyoning One-Day Adventure', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '3417-autosave-v1', '', '', '2016-08-07 23:24:58', '2016-08-07 23:24:58', '', 3417, 'http://dac.technocreates.net/nepalayaexplorer/2016/08/07/3417-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
