(3705, 1, '2018-05-08 05:26:15', '2018-05-08 05:26:15', '<div class=\"one withsmallpadding \" ><div class=\"page_content_wrapper\"></p>\n<div style=\"text-align:center\">\n<h2 class=\"ppb_title\">Welcome to Asia with Nepalaya Explorer</h2>\n<div class=\"page_caption_desc\"></div>\n</div>\n<p>\n	Simply speaking “we do only adventure”, Nepalaya Explorer is bespoke trailblazer premier Authentic Himalayan Outdoors , and provide tailor-made adventure holiday across Nepal &#038; Myanmar Himalayas. We are the team of dedicated adventure industry professionals who are all passionate about Adventure. Our passion is our business; over two decades of guiding experience in adventure tourism field in Nepal and Myanmar and still do so. Our first priority is to ensure that you don’t just do the adventure… you experience the adventure. Don’t be fooled by others offering “one stop” online shopping only to be shuffled among the true providers once you arrive. Nepalaya Explorer has created an entire life around taking people in both Himalayas. First we listen to what you want out of trip and, give us your time frame, date and budget, and then we carefully and perfectly design an individual tailor-made holiday adventure to match your time frame, working to your budget and with an absolute commitment in quality and safety to suits your exact requirements and explores your interests’ places at your own speed. Quite simply, we do it better and safer because it matters more to us and it is our driving passion and single commitment. Our holidays are all about excitement, and journey through the natural beauty and cultural diversity of some of the planet’s remotest areas. We’ll guide you up to the most exciting wilderness Himalaya and introduce you to our favorite destinations in style with safety. There’s no set recipe either fix date- they’re tailor-made down to the finest detail around Travelers tastes and interests. We work with genuine locally-owned services wherever possible apart from our own trips.\n</p>\n<p>\n	<strong>Your Adventure-Your Way. </strong>Far more than just a catchy and flexible in our Slogan, Level of difficulty and style of adventure are tailored to your ability level so with us you’re the principle of choosing your own adventure that you have dreamed and imagine. We are good listener! We believe that the best adventure is created through collaboration. We are thrilled to have the ability to offer such a wide variety of trips. We also realize that this can create confusion. We are a fantastic resource and look forward to helping you choose the trip that is perfect for you and your group. Please feel free to call or email with any questions you might have, we love to help. Often after a brief conversation with one of our staff the answers become clear. So we ensure that our staff complements your ideas, instead of overriding them. We provide the structure to your journey, offered new type of travel adventure- Get inspired by the adventure ideas on our website. Then speak to us for first-hand adventure expert advice and if you&#8217;re ready, start planning your trip in detail.\n</p>\n<p>\n	<strong>We work hard to provide an experience that is more than any multi day’s adventure trip or a day spent. </strong>We will design a trip around you, strive to offer real insight the untouched nature, people and their culture, and away from crowds, even commercial route we do different and unique way, and show you the real highlights in a different light, and introduce you to places and experience that others never been and many might are missing, We strive to ensure that time spent with us is time that you will always look back on fondly. We want to leave you with memories that bring a smile to your face no matter where you are, no matter what you are doing, no matter how much time has passed and no matter how far you are from your Home sweet Home.\n</p>\n<p>\n	<strong>We pride ourselves in the quality of our trips and our ability to work with our guests. </strong>Since the spring of 2013 Nepalaya Explorer has been offering the finest authentic outdoor adventures available, period. In an industry that is often about tight schedules and ordering your adventure by the numbers Nepalaya Explorer is more than happy to customize any of our trips in Nepal and Myanmar.\n</p>\n<p>\n	<strong>We are willing to work with the guest to provide exactly what they envision.</strong> We’ve had the opportunity to organized family friendly adventure that suits for your little one and the elderly parents, newlyweds honeymoon and anniversary trip in Himalaya, Himalaya yoga and meditation trek, corporate team building events, Himalayan Community Trek which we provides health, education, sports with multi play grounds, educating people and children about Rubbish management knowledge from their very little age and encourage them in environmental campaign. We have designed and run specialized training courses to become a mountain, trekking, rafting and just multi adventure guide, National and International Army training, expeditions and youth leadership programs that offer students adventures and learning experience in a world they couldn&#8217;t imagine existed. We have helped major international and national universities with trips focused on adventure, geology, photography and creative writing. We’ve hosted, organized and supported the national and international adventure movie makers and journalists and World Charity Trip for disable children to orphanage house and association from around the world. We did these trips not because we offered them, we did these trips because we love to and you asked.\n</p>\n<p>\n	<strong>We are owned and operated by our guides with staffed and people who make their living in the Himalaya outdoors.</strong> Again, No matter the season you’ll find the owners, guides and staff in outdoors in Nepal and Myanmar Himalaya. The reason we run adventure is because we love nature. So we climb mountains, trek to the base camps, whitewater rafting and kayaking, rock climbing, canyoning, caving, mountain bike, mountain flight, paragliding, bungee jumping, wildlife safari, “Myanmar Source to the Sea or Sea to the Source Adventure Journey” and share adventure experiences with both old and new friends (that’s you!). Our trips are designed and run in the spirit of providing the highest quality experience and spreading our passion for our mountains and rivers, not to maximize our profit margins. We like to make this evident from the moment our guests walk in our door and experience the atmosphere of authentic adventure journey through Nepal and Myanmar, until they hug us and goodbye at the end of the trip and until we meet again! The kind of authenticity and hospitality you&#8217;ll find here can&#8217;t be faked because we work from our heart. Come and see for yourself, or meet our team here. In short, we love the outdoors adventure.\n</p>\n<p>\n	<strong>We have a tremendous amount of experience and expertise.</strong> Put simply and telling the truth, our trips come after decades of working and exploring experience in adventure field in both countries as an adventure guide. We’ve been there done that and become better for it.  our love and experience of wild places and our constant desire to be outside, we have gained a knowledge base that can’t be won through school or training alone. Mother Nature is our first teacher and Himalayas is our classroom and playground (which makes us among the luckiest people in the world).\n</p>\n<p>\n	<strong><br />\n		We have extensive knowledge of and certification in mountain climbing safety, techniques and dealing with high altitude sickness, wilderness first aid and CPR, whitewater rescue, safety and technique.</strong> In addition to a deep reservoir of personal experience, each of our adventure guides is licensed by the Nepal &#038; Myanmar Mountaineering Association, Trekking Agencies Association of Nepal, Nepal Association of Rafting Agencies, Nepal Kayak &#038; Canoe Club and International Rafting Federation certified Grade 4/5 raft guides, trip leaders and kayakers, swift water certified and insured. Our climbing guides are NRCS certified for the terrain they operate in. Our guides are intimately acquainted with not only the mountain, river and rock, but also the incredible surroundings of the Himalaya wilderness places and with local communities in both Nepal and Myanmar.\n</p>\n<p>\n	<strong>We take your adventure seriously. </strong>Far more than just a catchy slogan, in reality adventure is all about <strong>Risk &#038; Fun</strong>, So there for it is our core philosophy and acknowledges our role as professionals in providing fun and safe adventures (which makes us among the luckiest people in the world, we are well aware!) in an environment that demands serious skill, experience, and judgment. The mountain we climb, trails we trek and rivers in which we paddle are wild, remote, untouched, and subject to the unpredictability of nature, and weather meaning that safety is far from automatic and risks need to be properly managed. It goes without saying that safety is always our first and unforgotten priority in all of our activities. This commitment runs through every part of our outdoors adventure operation, from the equipment we provide, to the professionalism of our guides, to the way we run our trips and selecting our local and international partners. This is the key ingredient in our Himalayan homegrown recipe for serious fun!\n</p>\n<p>\n	<strong>Our love, respect and role for nature and peoples throughout adventure, </strong>As an Adventure person, relationship with the nature is one that few others can truly understand. The Himalayas, for all its massive mountains peaks and impressive geography, is actually an incredibly fragile environment. Deforestation, erosion and overpopulation in the mountains regions are becoming major problems in some areas. Adventure tourism, which has given new opportunities and resources, has also had a large effect on the consumption of natural resources. Our lives have revolved around rivers, mountain and people. These areas have captivated our imagination and our hearts, and throughout all the years inspired us. For over two decades of adventure running experience we have gaining knowledge and appreciation for those little known areas. In our daily lives, Mother Nature reigns supreme— she seduces us with her beauty, awes us with her might, and charms us with her style. What she often fails to show us is how vulnerable she really is and how much our actions hurt her. She depends on those who know her best to help others understand and respect her needs. Here we recognize our duty to educate and inspire every one of our guests through one-of-a-kind adventure experiences. In this way we strive to play a powerful role in raising awareness, shaping attitudes, and improving the ways in which we collectively interact with nature. Nepal and Myanmar wilderness is experience unprecedented threat from explosive growth in adventure tourism and local economic ambitions. Again, there are few environmental laws to regulate the ways in which companies practice, and even fewer authorities to enforce them. The result is, again a &#8220;self-governed&#8221; industry that depends greatly on its leaders to maintain a culture of environmental integrity by setting good examples. Again we recognize and honor, and fell more and more an increased responsibility to protect and preserved these wild places and this is the message we convey to everyone. It is of the utmost importance to all of us that our interaction with the people we encounter along the way be positive and mutually beneficial and we treat every area as if it was our home. We provide real benefits to local economy, employing and training staff, purchasing all supplies and services locally, and supporting people in the areas we visit for sustainable development with providing such as medical, education, sports, environment campaign in community and providing dustbin. Why is this so important to us? Because adventure was once our passion before it was our business. Today, it still is. Nepalaya Explorer has taken significant steps towards the protection of the Himalayan environment and the people who live here. If you would like to know how you can help, please contact us because we are running our Himalayan Community Project (HCP) for Sustainable Development in rural areas as well as badly damage villages by April 2015 Earthquake in Nepal.\n</p>\n<p>\n	<strong>Our goal is to make your vacation especial. </strong>Through sharing our love and passion of the outdoors adventures, mountains, rock, rivers and jungles and the incredible both countries through which they run we hope to make authentic holidays adventure and Nepalaya Explorer places that you will want to return to again and again.\n</p>\n<p>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"one withpadding ppb_team \" style=\"background:#f3f3f3;\" ><div class=\"page_content_wrapper\" style=\"text-align:center\"><h2 class=\"ppb_title\">Our Team</h2><br/><br/><div class=\"team_wrapper\"><div class=\"one_fourth animated1 \"><div class=\"post_img static team animate \" style=\"margin-bottom:10px\"><img class=\"team_pic\" src=\"http://dac.technocreates.net/nepalayaexplorer/wp-includes/images/media/default.png\" alt=\"\"/></div><br class=\"clear\"/><div id=\"portfolio_desc_2625\" class=\"portfolio_desc team shortcode \"><h5>Deepak Nepal</h5><span class=\"portfolio_excerpt\">Guide</span><p>Need some info about the team here. Need some info about the team here. Need some info about the team here.</p><ul class=\"social_wrapper team\"><li><a title=\"Deepak Nepal on Twitter\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"tooltip\" href=\"http://twitter.com/#\"><i class=\"fa fa-twitter\"></i></a></li><li><a title=\"Deepak Nepal on Facebook\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"tooltip\" href=\"http://facebook.com/#\"><i class=\"fa fa-fa